    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-08T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-08T20:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/243: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="to"
                            >Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-08T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 8, 1932—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. For <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Reber</persName>. The substance of
                    Department’s telegram No. 77, May 8, 1 p.m., has been communicated to <persName
                        corresp="#p_FHSJ1">Harvey Firestone, Junior</persName>. He stated that our
                    opinion as to the requirements precedent to serious discussion by them of any
                    proposal involving either a modification <pb facs="0815" n="725" xml:id="pg_725"
                    /> of the loan contract or further advances represented in his view a
                    “conservative estimate”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
